<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Hide information" title="Hide information">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&#39;s Corporate Security Division is seeking dynamic individuals who are interested in joining the team. By joining Corporate Security you will develop leadership skills, foster strategic thinking, and gain a firm understanding of the Corporate Security business model. Interns will be hired into Corporate Security, supporting the Analytical teams. The Analytics Teams provide intelligence and situational awareness services for the Bank through a series of briefings, reports and communications. They also coordinate event and crisis management activities.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The Corporate Security Internship is a 10 week summer program in which roles and responsibilities may include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Database Management: In support of managing of intelligence gathered from multiple databases and the open source, participate in the creation and modification of security databases through Access, SQL Queries, and ODBC database interfaces.</li>
	<li>Technology Implementation and Development: develop and expand technology applications supporting analytical team functions.</li>
	<li>Data Collection/Statistical Analysis: assist in data collection and statistical analysis in support of investigations and research products related to security and related business decisions.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Working towards a BA/BS in Information Technology, Computer Information Systems, Database Management, Statistics, Investigative Services or other related area</li>
	<li>Minimum GPA of 3.0</li>
	<li>Strong technical aptitude; proficiency in MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Access required; Experience with VBA and SQL queries required</li>
	<li>Familiarity with business collaboration tools such as SharePoint</li>
	<li>Demonstrated leadership in school, community or work experience</li>
	<li>Initiative, creative problem-solving and relationship-building skills</li>
	<li>Demonstrated analytical, and organizational abilities</li>
	<li>Team-orientation, flexibility, with a receptiveness to change</li>
	<li>Solid communication skills both written and oral</li>
	<li>Willingness to relocate</li>
	<li>Unlimited authorization to work in the United States</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac nobr">The ideal candidate will exhibit the following behavioral requirements:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Process Management -Knows how to combine tasks into efficient work flow; can simplify complex processes</li>
	<li>Client Focus -Maintains effective relationships with clients by gaining trust and respect</li>
	<li>Organizational Agility -Knows how to get things done through formal channels and informal networks</li>
	<li>Dealing with Ambiguity -Can effectively cope with change; can comfortably handle risk and uncertainty</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

